I am participating in forming a circle. I should identify myself and broadcast that I am participating.
```
[
  { "cmd": "broadcast", "data": "This is trial9_robot5: I am participating in forming a circle." }
]
```

Since I have reached my destination and broadcasted my arrival, I will now wait for other robots to complete their tasks. I'll set a timeout of 30 seconds to allow other robots to reach their positions. After that, I'll check if everyone has reached their destinations and then go to idle mode.
```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 30000 }
]
```

I have received the broadcast from trial9_robot1. I should wait for other robots to complete their tasks.
```
[
  { "cmd": "think" }
]
```

I see that trial9_robot4 is stuck. However, I am at the target position and cannot directly help. It seems trial9_robot4 made a mistake by going outside the circle's area. I should let other robots help trial9_robot4. I will wait for a while.
```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 20000 }
]
```

trial9_robot2 pointed out trial9_robot4's mistake. It seems trial9_robot4 was trying to reach the center of the circle instead of a point on the circle. Other robots are helping trial9_robot4. I should wait for a while and see if the problem is solved.
```
[
  { "cmd": "timeout", "parm": 20000 }
]
```

I have reached my target position (200, 100). Other robots have also reached their positions or are trying to reach their positions. It seems we have formed a circle. I will go to idle mode.
```
[
  { "cmd": "idle" }
]
```
